Honey, we talked about this.

04:24.848 --> 04:26.307
We can't fly you back here

04:24.848 --> 04:26.307
in the middle of the week.

04:26.349 --> 04:27.726
You'd only be here

04:26.349 --> 04:27.726
for eight hours.

04:27.768 --> 04:28.727
But, Mom...

04:27.768 --> 04:28.727
Sweetie, I'm sorry.

04:28.769 --> 04:30.104
I wish things were different,

04:30.145 --> 04:31.312
but you were just home

04:30.145 --> 04:31.312
for Thanksgiving,

04:31.354 --> 04:33.148
and that's all

04:31.354 --> 04:33.148
we can afford right now.

04:33.190 --> 04:35.567
Mom, you don't know what they do

04:33.190 --> 04:35.567
to people around here on their

04:35.609 --> 04:36.735
(whispering):

04:35.609 --> 04:36.735
birthday.

04:36.777 --> 04:38.237
They strip you naked,

04:38.278 --> 04:39.905
and they shave every hair

04:38.278 --> 04:39.905
off your body

04:39.947 --> 04:41.740
and they throw you

04:39.947 --> 04:41.740
in the reflecting pond.

04:41.782 --> 04:43.158
Is that what you want for me?

04:43.200 --> 04:44.785
I'm impressed, Francis.

04:44.826 --> 04:46.703
Your stories are getting better;

04:44.826 --> 04:46.703
at least more believable.

04:46.745 --> 04:48.205
What stories?

04:48.247 --> 04:49.998
Oh, when you wanted to come home

04:48.247 --> 04:49.998
for that party

04:50.040 --> 04:51.750
and you swore the academy

04:50.040 --> 04:51.750
was being terrorized

04:51.792 --> 04:52.751
by a pack of feral dogs?

04:52.793 --> 04:54.962
Which were never caught.

04:55.003 --> 04:56.922
Francis, I want you home

04:55.003 --> 04:56.922
for your birthday, too,

04:56.964 --> 04:59.007
but we just can't afford it.

04:59.049 --> 05:01.342
Fine. I guess I'll just

04:59.049 --> 05:01.342
fend for myself

05:01.384 --> 05:03.804
and hope these monsters

05:01.384 --> 05:03.804
don't find out it's my...

05:03.845 --> 05:05.222
(whispering):

05:03.845 --> 05:05.222
you know.

05:05.264 --> 05:07.348
(cadet screaming)

05:07.390 --> 05:09.810
He's still got an eyebrow!

05:09.851 --> 05:11.311
Get him!

05:15.065 --> 05:16.275
Hey, Malcolm.

05:16.316 --> 05:18.359
I heard about your brother

05:16.316 --> 05:18.359
last night.

05:18.401 --> 05:19.527
It was hilarious.

05:19.569 --> 05:20.612
You didn't see it?

05:20.654 --> 05:23.364
A sporting... event?

05:23.406 --> 05:24.950
Right. I wonder

05:23.406 --> 05:24.950
what it's like

05:24.992 --> 05:26.534
to get beat up

05:24.992 --> 05:26.534
by a girl.

05:26.576 --> 05:28.369
It's totally humiliating.

05:28.411 --> 05:29.830
You just want to die.

05:29.871 --> 05:31.748
Your brother didn't

05:29.871 --> 05:31.748
soil himself, did he?

05:31.790 --> 05:33.792
No.

05:33.834 --> 05:35.210
Neither did I.

05:35.252 --> 05:36.377
You know...

05:36.419 --> 05:38.297
Reese's embarrassing

05:36.419 --> 05:38.297
defeat could have

05:38.337 --> 05:39.631
serious consequences

05:38.337 --> 05:39.631
for us all.

05:39.673 --> 05:41.466
He'll be working

05:39.673 --> 05:41.466
extra hard

05:41.508 --> 05:43.384
to prove he's still on top

05:41.508 --> 05:43.384
of the food chain.

05:43.426 --> 05:45.553
You're saying we could

05:43.426 --> 05:45.553
actually have a meaner,

05:45.595 --> 05:47.388
more vicious Reese on our hands?

05:47.430 --> 05:48.389
It's very possible.

05:48.431 --> 05:49.683
We can't avoid

05:48.431 --> 05:49.683
the beatings,

05:49.724 --> 05:51.768
but I suggest that,

05:49.724 --> 05:51.768
as a wedgie deterrent,

05:51.810 --> 05:53.895
we go without underwear

05:51.810 --> 05:53.895
for the next several days.

05:53.937 --> 05:55.438
Uh-oh.

05:55.480 --> 05:56.815
Here he comes now.

05:59.358 --> 06:01.360
