06:07.450 --> 06:10.369
This is the first time

06:07.450 --> 06:10.369
I've ever been happy to be me.

06:16.459 --> 06:18.377
You want something

06:16.459 --> 06:18.377
to look at?

06:21.380 --> 06:23.382
I'll give you something

06:21.380 --> 06:23.382
to look at.

06:24.383 --> 06:25.635
(screaming)

06:38.481 --> 06:40.817
The old

06:38.481 --> 06:40.817
chocolate milk diversion.

06:40.859 --> 06:42.652
Wish I had thought of that.

06:45.864 --> 06:48.449
Okay, what the hell was that

06:45.864 --> 06:48.449
milk thing on the playground?

06:48.491 --> 06:50.077
I don't know.

06:48.491 --> 06:50.077
I had to do something.

06:50.118 --> 06:52.079
So you poured milk on yourself?

06:52.120 --> 06:54.373
Why didn't you

06:52.120 --> 06:54.373
just pound that kid?

06:54.413 --> 06:55.540
Because I'm sick of doing that.

06:55.582 --> 06:57.458
I'm sick of beating up

06:55.582 --> 06:57.458
little kids.

06:57.500 --> 06:59.044
It's creepy.

06:59.086 --> 07:00.837
But that's you--

06:59.086 --> 07:00.837
that's what you do.

07:00.879 --> 07:01.838
Not anymore.

07:01.880 --> 07:03.298
That was the old me.

07:03.340 --> 07:04.465
The thing I did

07:03.340 --> 07:04.465
at school today

07:04.507 --> 07:06.509
was me destroying the old Reese.

07:06.551 --> 07:08.678
So, drenching yourself

07:06.551 --> 07:08.678
with chocolate milk

07:08.720 --> 07:10.471
was like a baptism?

07:10.513 --> 07:12.099
No, idiot.

07:12.140 --> 07:13.975
I was washing away

07:12.140 --> 07:13.975
the old me and starting over.

07:14.017 --> 07:15.769
You know, you've been acting

07:14.017 --> 07:15.769
really weird

07:15.810 --> 07:18.188
ever since you got your butt

07:15.810 --> 07:18.188
kicked by that girl.

07:18.230 --> 07:19.564
It's not just about the girl.

07:19.606 --> 07:21.858
Wrestling made me

07:19.606 --> 07:21.858
feel good, you know?

07:21.900 --> 07:23.484
I was helping the school.

07:23.526 --> 07:25.320
People looked up to me.

07:25.362 --> 07:27.406
And that's gone now,

07:25.362 --> 07:27.406
and I've got nothing.

07:27.447 --> 07:29.490
But it's not going

07:27.447 --> 07:29.490
to be like that anymore.

07:29.532 --> 07:32.493
I'm going to find a way to make

07:29.532 --> 07:32.493
people proud of me again.

07:32.535 --> 07:34.121
So what are you going to do?

07:34.162 --> 07:35.289
I don't know.

07:35.330 --> 07:37.374
I just want to be

07:35.330 --> 07:37.374
the good guy,

07:37.416 --> 07:38.959
do good stuff...

07:39.000 --> 07:41.128
for good.

07:41.169 --> 07:42.754
Dewey, what can I

07:41.169 --> 07:42.754
do for you?

07:42.796 --> 07:44.298
Mom!

07:42.796 --> 07:44.298
Shut up!

07:44.339 --> 07:46.216
I'm trying to help you.

07:44.339 --> 07:46.216
(grunting)

07:49.261 --> 07:51.763
Hi, sweetie.

07:51.805 --> 07:53.181
What's wrong?

07:53.223 --> 07:54.599
Is it Francis?

07:54.641 --> 07:56.517
Yeah.

07:56.559 --> 07:57.894
He keeps calling.

07:57.936 --> 07:59.520
His stupid stories are

07:57.936 --> 07:59.520
touching, in a way.

07:59.562 --> 08:01.440
You know, he just

07:59.562 --> 08:01.440
wants to come home.

08:01.481 --> 08:03.900
It's the first time he's

08:01.481 --> 08:03.900
been away on his birthday.

08:03.942 --> 08:05.986
Well, maybe we can at least

08:03.942 --> 08:05.986
do something that night

08:06.027 --> 08:07.528
to take our minds off it.

08:07.570 --> 08:11.532
A guy at work won these

08:07.570 --> 08:11.532
concert tickets on the radio.

08:11.574 --> 08:12.742
Jimmy Buffett?

08:12.784 --> 08:14.911
He didn't want them.

08:12.784 --> 08:14.911
Can you imagine?

08:14.953 --> 08:17.038
(phone ringing)

08:17.080 --> 08:19.040
Hello.

08:19.082 --> 08:21.751
Mom, great news. I figured out

08:19.082 --> 08:21.751
a way to get home Wednesday.

08:21.793 --> 08:22.794
Francis...

08:22.836 --> 08:24.463
No, it won't cost you a cent.

08:24.504 --> 08:26.173
One of the cadet's fathers

08:24.504 --> 08:26.173
is a trucker.

08:26.214 --> 08:28.258
He said I can ride

08:26.214 --> 08:28.258
in the refrigerator compartment

08:28.300 --> 08:30.718
to the 609 interchange.

08:28.300 --> 08:30.718
And a buddy of his

08:30.760 --> 08:32.387
flies a crop duster.

08:30.760 --> 08:32.387
Now, if he's sober,

08:32.429 --> 08:34.555
he should be able to drop me off

08:32.429 --> 08:34.555
at the soybean field

08:34.597 --> 08:35.556
near the train station...

08:35.598 --> 08:36.850
Honey, Francis, come on.

08:36.891 --> 08:38.435
There'll be other birthdays.

08:38.477 --> 08:41.146
Ask him if he wants a T-shirt

08:38.477 --> 08:41.146
from the concert.

08:41.188 --> 08:42.147
What concert?

08:42.189 --> 08:43.564
Uh, your father

08:43.606 --> 08:44.858
got us tickets

08:43.606 --> 08:44.858
to see Jimmy Buffett.

08:44.899 --> 08:46.485
And this concert wouldn't happen

08:46.526 --> 08:48.028
to be on Wednesday night,

08:46.526 --> 08:48.028
would it?

08:48.069 --> 08:49.570
My birthday?

08:49.612 --> 08:51.572
Uh, yes, it is,

08:49.612 --> 08:51.572
but that has nothing to do...

08:51.614 --> 08:52.991
Oh, now I get it.

08:53.033 --> 08:54.451
You can't afford

08:53.033 --> 08:54.451
to bring me home, but somehow

08:54.493 --> 08:55.952
you find money

08:54.493 --> 08:55.952
for Jimmy Buffett tickets.

08:55.994 --> 08:58.497
Francis, that's not

08:55.994 --> 08:58.497
the way it is at all.

08:58.538 --> 09:00.165
They were free tickets.

08:58.538 --> 09:00.165
Sure they were.

09:00.207 --> 09:01.875
A friend of your father's

09:00.207 --> 09:01.875
gave them to us.

09:01.916 --> 09:02.959
He's not really a friend.

09:03.001 --> 09:04.627
You know, you guys should really

09:04.669 --> 09:07.755
get your stories straight before

09:04.669 --> 09:07.755
you try to ditch me on my...

09:07.797 --> 09:09.132
(whispering):

09:07.797 --> 09:09.132
birthday.

09:14.637 --> 09:16.181
Hey, Malcolm.

09:16.223 --> 09:18.599
Want my cake?

09:16.223 --> 09:18.599
You're not hungry?

09:18.641 --> 09:21.602
No. I ate my lunch

09:18.641 --> 09:21.602
and  my decoy lunch.

09:21.644 --> 09:24.231
Now that Reese isn't

09:21.644 --> 09:24.231
stealing it anymore, I get both.

09:24.272 --> 09:26.774
And Reese hasn't made me

09:24.272 --> 09:26.774
eat grass for a week.

09:26.816 --> 09:28.609
Everything tastes better.

09:28.651 --> 09:31.530
Life... is good.

09:31.571 --> 09:35.867
I've been taking ballet,

09:31.571 --> 09:35.867
and I don't care who knows it.

09:35.909 --> 09:37.285
Good for you.

09:38.828 --> 09:41.498
Two days ago,

09:38.828 --> 09:41.498
Reese would've creamed that kid.

09:41.540 --> 09:42.916
Things are really changing.

09:42.957 --> 09:45.626
It's like we've entered

09:42.957 --> 09:45.626
an age of enlightenment.

09:45.668 --> 09:47.295
It's kind of nice.

09:47.337 --> 09:48.922
Hey!

09:48.963 --> 09:50.507
Hey.

09:50.549 --> 09:52.509
What was that for?

09:52.551 --> 09:53.634
That's for having

09:52.551 --> 09:53.634
a smart mouth

09:53.676 --> 09:55.095
and making fun of me

09:53.676 --> 09:55.095
all the time.

09:55.136 --> 09:57.472
Since Reese

09:55.136 --> 09:57.472
is out of the picture,

09:57.514 --> 09:59.057
I don't have to take it anymore.

09:59.099 --> 10:00.517
What are you talking about?

10:00.559 --> 10:02.018
Now that your brother's a wuss,

10:02.060 --> 10:04.645
I don't have to worry

10:02.060 --> 10:04.645
about him coming after me

10:04.687 --> 10:05.939
when I teach you a lesson.

10:05.980 --> 10:07.065
But we're friends.

10:07.107 --> 10:09.025
Making cracks about me

10:07.107 --> 10:09.025
painting my face

10:09.067 --> 10:10.110
and being stupid?

10:10.151 --> 10:11.736
You say those things

10:10.151 --> 10:11.736
to  friends?

10:11.778 --> 10:13.654
Those things were funny.

10:13.696 --> 10:14.655
Oh, yeah. Real funny.

10:14.697 --> 10:16.074
I'll show you what's funny.

10:16.116 --> 10:17.867
Knock, knock. Who's there?

10:19.619 --> 10:20.661
Pushy Pusherson.

10:22.705 --> 10:23.623
What's wrong with him?

10:24.583 --> 10:25.666
(grunts)

10:25.708 --> 10:28.086
Remember me? Moby Rick?

10:28.128 --> 10:29.921
That was so hilarious.

10:29.963 --> 10:31.590
I never called you Moby Rick.

10:31.631 --> 10:32.924
I called you Rick-Oppotamus.

10:32.966 --> 10:33.674
Although...

10:33.716 --> 10:35.051
(grunting)

10:35.093 --> 10:36.344
Hey! Hey!

10:36.386 --> 10:37.429
Just wait for a second.

10:39.806 --> 10:42.183
So you guys really

10:39.806 --> 10:42.183
don't think I'm funny?

10:47.439 --> 10:49.649
Well, you learn something new

10:47.439 --> 10:49.649
every day.

10:52.110 --> 10:54.488
Evidently, I'm not as charming

10:52.110 --> 10:54.488
